	<key>readme</key>
	<string>## Proton Pass for Alfred

Search and copy passwords from your Proton Pass vault.

### Setup
1. Install pass-cli: `curl -fsSL https://proton.me/download/pass-cli/install.sh | bash`
2. Login: `pass-cli login`
3. Use `pp` keyword in Alfred

### Usage
- `pp &lt;query&gt;` — Search items
- `↩ Enter` — Open URL (or copy password if no URL)
- `⌃ Ctrl+Enter` — Copy password
- `⌥ Opt+Enter` — Copy username
- `⇧ Shift+Enter` — Copy TOTP code
- `⌘ Cmd+Enter` — Copy URL

### Commands
- `pp :setup` — Check CLI status
- `pp :refresh` — Clear cache

### Configuration
Set in Alfred Workflow Environment Variables:
- `CLIPBOARD_CLEAR_SECONDS` — Auto-clear clipboard after N seconds (default: 30)
- `PASS_CLI_PATH` — Custom path to pass-cli binary (default: auto-detect)
- `VAULT_NAME` — Vault name(s) to search, comma-separated (default: all vaults)

### Commands
- `pp :vault` — Show available vaults</string>
